The shipping method and service you select will also impact the cost of Alaska car transport. Commonly used auto transport services in Alaska include:
<br><br>
<strong>Open auto transport: </strong>Your vehicle will be on an open, two-tiered transport trailer with multiple cars. This option is typically not recommended due to the frigid climate in Alaska, but it is the cheapest and most popular method of auto transport.
<br><br>
<strong>Enclosed auto transport: </strong>Your vehicle will be loaded into a completely enclosed trailer and shielded from the elements during <a href="https://rapidautoshipping.com/services/enclosed-shipping" target="_blank"><strong>enclosed auto transport</strong></a>. This option is favoured for Alaska car transport because your car will be protected from the state's severe climate.
<br><br>
<strong>Terminal to terminal transport: </strong>This is a good choice for cheap car shipping compared to door-to-door transportation because your car will be dropped off and picked up at the terminals closest to your final destination. Even though door-to-door shipping is standard, it's rarely offered in Alaska.
