<h2><strong>How To Transport A Car Legally to Alaska?</strong></h2>
Before you hire an Alaska car transport company, you should learn about the rules for registering vehicles in Alaska. If you want to live in Alaska, you have to register your car within ten days of getting there. If not, non-residents can drive a car from another state for 60 days.
<br><br>
You must also have the proper paperwork to get your car to or from Alaska, like a license and registration. Since cars going to Alaska are shipped, fire rules say you can't have more than a quarter of a gas tank in your vehicle before moving it. Cars must also be ready to go and have their lights turned off.
